Insertion site (context only — Linguist's `languages.yml` is alphabetised
on the top-level keys, so place `Glyph:` between `Glsl:` and
`Glyph Bitmap Distribution Format:`):

 Glsl:
   type: programming
   color: "#5686a5"
   extensions:
   - ".glsl"
   ace_mode: glsl
   tm_scope: source.glsl
   language_id: 137
+Glyph:
+  type: programming
+  color: "#1FA9A0"
+  extensions:
+  - ".glyph"
+  tm_scope: none
+  ace_mode: text
+  language_id: 999100001
 Glyph Bitmap Distribution Format:
   type: data
   color: "#000000"
   extensions:
   - ".bdf"
   tm_scope: source.bdf
   ace_mode: text
   language_id: 99

Notes:
- `language_id` is a placeholder. Linguist reviewers will assign the
  final ID by running `script/update-ids` against their local
  registry. The chosen value (`999100001`) is far enough above
  current IDs to avoid collision in a hand-applied patch.
- The `Glsl` and `Glyph Bitmap Distribution Format` entries are
  reproduced from Linguist's current `languages.yml` for context;
  do not modify them when applying this patch.
